===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A hand-held narrow rod, usually used for pointing or instructing, or as a traditional emblem of authority.
#* {{quote-book|1=en|year=1887|author=H. Rider Haggard|authorlink=H. Rider Haggard|title=She: A History of Adventure|url=http://www.gutenberg.org/files/3155/3155-0.txt|passage=Then all of a sudden a number of armed men arranged in companies, and marshalled by officers who held ivory '''wands''' in their hands, came running swiftly towards us, having, so far as I could make out, emerged from the face of the precipice like ants from their burrows.}}
# {{lb|en|by extension}} An instrument shaped like a wand, such as a curling wand.
# A stick or rod used by a magician (a [[magic wand]]), [[conjurer]] or [[diviner]] ([[divining rod]]).
#* '''1859''', {{w|George Meredith}}, ''The Ordeal of Richard Feverel'', Chapter 13:
#*: Love is that blessed '''wand''' which wins the waters from the hardness of the heart.
# A stick, branch, or stalk, especially of [[willow]].
#* {{RQ:Shakespeare Merchant of Venice|act=I|scene=iii|passage=The skillful shepherd peeled me certain '''wands'''.}}
#* {{quote-book|1=en|year=1891|author={{w|Thomas Hardy}}|title={{w|Tess of the d'Urbervilles}}|publisher=James R. Osgood, McIlvaine and Co.|location=London|volume=1|page=17|passage=In addition to the distinction of a white frock, every woman and girl carried in her right hand a peeled willow-'''wand''', and in her left a bunch of white flowers.}}
# A card of a particular [[suit]] of the [[minor arcana]] in [[tarot]], the wands.

